### [The Basics Of The Finger Command On Linux](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8EwR64jMvYw)
Deprecated but still useful for historical context.
- Basic usage of `finger` to display the logged-in user details.
- Enhanced usage with additional flags like `-m` for more detailed user information.
- How users can create `.project` and `.plan` files in their home directory to share information like their plans, phone numbers, or office hours.

```bash
finger
cat << EOF > ~/.project
   My project is learning the Linux terminal commands.
EOF
cat << EOF > ~/.plan
- Record tutorials every Monday, Wednesday, and Friday.
- Available for office hours 9 AM - 5 PM CST.
EOF

finger -m $USER
```
